# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Runtime (Vite `import.meta.env`)
#
# Variables prefixed with VITE_ are inlined into the production browser bundle
# at build time. They are NOT runtime secrets. Never put a production API key
# here — it will be readable by anyone who loads the page. See apps/web/README.md
# for more on the web-client auth story.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API origin used by the web client at runtime.
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/graphql

# API key sent with requests during local development.
# Use `seed-dev-key` to authenticate against the demo `seed` domain created
# by `npm run seed` (see scripts/README.md). This key is a well-known dev-only
# constant — do NOT reuse it in any production domain.
VITE_API_KEY=seed-dev-key

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build-time tooling (Node `process.env`, used by `npm run codegen`)
#
# These are read by apps/web/codegen.ts when introspecting the GraphQL schema.
# They are NOT used at app runtime and have sensible defaults matching the
# local-dev flow — only set them to override for a non-default environment
# (e.g., running codegen against a remote staging API).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# GraphQL endpoint the codegen introspects.
# CODEGEN_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/graphql

# API key sent to the endpoint during introspection.
# CODEGEN_API_KEY=seed-dev-key
